<div id="review_3863945315" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3863945315" />
    <a title="Nathan Lasson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/123868961-nathan-lasson"><img alt="Nathan Lasson" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3863945315?book_show_action=true">Feb 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nathan Lasson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nathan Lasson" href="/user/show/123868961-nathan-lasson">Nathan Lasson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20214789-truth-will-prevail">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3863945315&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3863945315" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4758364668429061644">For this month’s book review, I decided to read The Work and the Glory: Truth Shall Prevail, by Gerald Lund. I enjoyed reading the book for several reasons. First, I read and loved the first two books. Second, it was just as good as the first two. I enjoyed how the events in the history of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints were connected to those of the fictional threads of the story, such as Jessica’s involvement in Missouri. Lund’s excessive detail in some of the well-known event</span>
  <span id="freeText4758364668429061644" style="display:none">For this month’s book review, I decided to read The Work and the Glory: Truth Shall Prevail, by Gerald Lund. I enjoyed reading the book for several reasons. First, I read and loved the first two books. Second, it was just as good as the first two. I enjoyed how the events in the history of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints were connected to those of the fictional threads of the story, such as Jessica’s involvement in Missouri. Lund’s excessive detail in some of the well-known events of the previously mentioned Church is thrilling when mixed with his fictional characters. I especially enjoyed this since I have heard of several stories similar to the ones the previously mentioned characters carry. This is especially evident when Nathan leaves on his mission to Canada with several other famous leaders of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints. I thoroughly enjoyed the cliffhangers in the book, as they were well written, such as when Caroline walks up to Nathan’s door and introduces herself. I gave this book a five star rating due to how intricately it was woven into the history of the Latter-Day Saints.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4758364668429061644" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


